Class JDBCOutputFormat<OUT extends Tuple>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.flink.api.java.io.jdbc.JDBCOutputFormat<OUT>

    All Implemented Interfaces:

    public class JDBCOutputFormat<OUT extends Tuple>
extends Object
implements OutputFormat<OUT>
    OutputFormat to write tuples into a database. The OutputFormat has to be configured using the supplied OutputFormatBuilder.
    See Also:
    Tuple, DriverManager, Serialized Form

      • configure

        public void configure(Configuration parameters)
        Description copied from interface: OutputFormat
        Configures this output format. Since output formats are instantiated generically and hence parameterless, this method is the place where the output formats set their basic fields based on configuration values.

        This method is always called first on a newly instantiated output format.

        Specified by:
        configure in interface OutputFormat<OUT extends Tuple>
        Parameters:
        parameters - The configuration with all parameters.

        public void writeRecord(OUT tuple)
